    <h1>Startup</h1>
    <h2>Basic Path</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><p>The use case begins when the Inventory Manager starts the
	  application.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that a default database type has
	  been set.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks that the dbname and hostname
	  have been set if it's a MySQL database. Otherwise, if
	  it's a Sqlite database, the software checks that the folder name
	  and dbname have been set.</p></li>
      <li><p>Assuming the previous have not been set, the software prompts
	  for the whether to use a MySQL database or a
	  SQLite database.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software prompts for the database name and folder if
	  a Sqlite database, otherwise the software prompts for the
	  database name, host, user name, and password. </p></li>
      <li><p>If the database is a MySQL database, the software
	     prompts the Inventory Manager to login. Include <a href="Login.html">Login</a> </p>
      <li><p>The software connects to the database.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software checks whether the database schema
	  has been built.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software builds the database schema.</p></li>
	  

    <h2>Alternate Paths</h2>
    <h3>DB Error</h3>
  </body>

